@nickpan47, thanks for the referenced JIRA. 

I am considering breaking the  task of this SAMZA-205 into 4 steps:

1. Move hello-samza repo to samza-samples directory of samza repo;
2. Update the documentation related hello-samza to use the code in samza/samza-samples;
3. Delete hello-samza repo;
4. build a gradle target such as samzaSampleIntegrationTests to hook the tests in samza/samza-samples.

And this PR is the first step. After this one is done, 2&3 need to be done soon as well to bring it on par with the current situation. And 4 then can be done independently.
